<DESCRIPT>  CHILDREN; SF-BAY-AREA; FESTIVAL; LIST  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  THE fifth annual Children's Day Around the Bay telethon will be televised
Sunday on KRON-TV (Ch. 4) from 1 to 6 p.m. Unless otherwise indicated, those
are the hours the following events will take place. The public is invited to
participate at any of seven Bay Area sites:;    (box) The Lucile Salter
Packard Hospital at Stanford: Festivities begin at 11 a.m. and will include
performances by the Banana Slug String Band; the Smooth Operators, a rap group
from East Palo Alto, and gospel singer Tramaine Hawkins. There will be
appearances by two Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and the Cookie Monster. There
will be jugglers, roving artists and clowns. Gov. Pete Wilson will preside at
the 1:30 p.m. ribbon-cutting ceremony.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  ACTIVITY SCHEDULE FOR CHILDREN'S DAY AROUND
THE BAY  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>     (box) Great America Theme Park in Santa Clara: Special $4 discount
admission for anyone who brings a coupon being distributed by several
manufacturers. Jerry Graham and Jennifer Montana will greet kids brought to
the park from the hospital -- hospital kids will be at all the sites.
Coordinator at the park will be Jack Warren, managing partner of both of San
Jose's Last Laugh comedy clubs. There will be chuck-wagon races hosted by
Purina Dog Chow, and a group of Stanford Medical School students will
accompany patients on park rides.;    (box) PruneYard Shopping Center in
Campbell: Children's author Patricia Polacco will tell stories and young
Suzuki musicians will perform. There will be ice-cream-eating contests and a
waiters' race. A high-tech medical van for the new hospital will be unveiled.;
   (box) Ghirardelli Square in San Francisco: Make-A-Circus troupe will teach
kids how to dress up and act like a clown. There will also be face-painting
artists, ice-cream-eating contests and a chocolate festival.;    (box) Oakland
Coliseum: Sportscaster Gary Radnich will lead a group of patients from
Children's Hospital in a behind-the-scenes tour of the players' clubhouse and
the kids will meet some players. A big tailgate party will start at 3 p.m. The
Oakland A's will play the Seattle Mariners at 5 p.m.;    (box) Redwood Empire
Ice Arena in Santa Rosa: Olympic figure skater Debi Thomas and world class
skater Kristi Yamaguchi will perform. There will also be an exhibition by Team
Rollerblade and a hockey exhibition between Stanford and UC-Berkeley. Kids can
sculpt snow and meet Dominique DiPrima, star of the TV show "Home Turf.";   
(box) Concord Pavilion in Concord: The doors will open at 1:30 p.m. for a
concert featuring Nils Lofgren, Bad English, Enuff Z'Nuff, Toy Matinee, Little
Caesar and comedian Michael Pritchard. Tickets are $10 and $12.;    At 8 p.m.
tonight KRON will show a documentary called "Children of Courage," detailing
the struggles and joys of parents and children at the Stanford hospital.  </TEXT>
